# Archers vs Knights RT: Simulation Spec

## Overview

AvKrt adds a real-time visual layer on top of [AvK](../../avk/docs/SPEC.md). It uses the same rules as AvK. The game board is much smaller to represent visual states. The client advances one turn, then visualizes the turn over a specified period of time.

---

## Differences from AvK

### Board Size

Much smaller than AvK's 320x144.

### Archer Range

Archers have an attack range of 2 instead of AvK's 3.

---

## Turn Timing

A turn has a length in milliseconds. The default turn length is 1000ms. Turn length is stored as a component on an entity in the game world. Turn length is tunable in real time while playing.

All timing values are expressed in ms based on a default turn length of 1000ms but take longer or shorter depending on current game speed.

A turn is divided into four sequential phases. Phase durations are tuned based on a 1000ms budget, scaled by actual play rate. The phases are also tunable. The default breakdown:

| Phase | Duration |
|-------|----------|
| Movement | 250ms |
| Attack | 250ms |
| Reaction | 250ms |
| Defeat | 250ms |

---

## Two Worlds

The architecture follows an MVC pattern where each concern is its own ECS world. A ControllerWorld would complete the triad but is not yet defined.

### Model World

The Model World of AvKrt is exactly as the game world of AvK.

### View World

All state surrounding the visualization of turns lives in the View World. The View World contains information that is not relevant to gameplay but which is relevant to visualization. The View World contains data representations of the sprites in the Model World and their animation state.

---

## View World Data Model

### Sprite Sheets

A sprite sheet is a standalone entity in the View World. It contains image data and has no state. Many visual children reference the same sprite sheet. A sprite sheet is a sequence of equal-sized frames packed into a single image.

### VisualEntity

A VisualEntity is the View World representation of a Model World entity. It references a Model World entity by entity ID and inherits its location. A VisualEntity has a state (idle, moving, attacking, reacting, defeated) and an ordered list of children.

The children are visual components (body, weapon, etc.). The order of children in the parent determines draw order ÔÇö first child draws first (bottom), last child draws on top.

### Children

Each child may have an offset expressed as a displacement from the parent entity's location. A child has an animation state that references a sprite sheet and holds playback state (current frame, which animation is playing). A child also has state animations ÔÇö a mapping of parent state to frame range (first frame, last frame) within its sprite sheet. When the parent VisualEntity enters a state, each child looks up its frame range for that state. If a child has no animation defined for a state, it is not rendered during that state.

For example, during the defeated state the body child has a shrink animation so it renders. The weapon child has no defeated animation defined, so it disappears.

### Sprites and Animations

A sprite is an animation. An animation with a single frame is a static sprite. There is no distinction between the two.

In an animation all frames must have the same dimensions. A sprite animation is defined by a first frame, a last frame, and a duration. When playing an animation we know the first frame, the last frame, and the duration, which lets us know what frame should be playing at any time.

A single sprite sheet can be used by multiple animations with different indexes for first and last frame.

### Config Entity

A singleton config entity holds turn timing and phase state:
- Turn timing ÔÇö turn_length_ms, movement_ms, attack_ms, reaction_ms, defeat_ms
- Phase state ÔÇö current phase (enum), elapsed_ms within the current phase

---

## View World Systems

### TurnCapture

Runs once after the Model World advances a turn. For each game unit: reads previous position from rewind history, copies Weapon.attacked to the VisualEntity, checks TookDamage, checks health <= 0. Creates and destroys VisualEntities to match the Model World population. Sets all VisualEntity states to the first phase (movement).

### PhaseAdvance

Runs every frame. Increments phase elapsed_ms by delta time. When elapsed >= phase duration, advances to the next phase and updates all VisualEntity states accordingly. After all four phases complete, signals the Model World to advance the next turn.

### Animation

Runs every frame. For every visual child, looks up the parent's current state in the child's state animations. If a mapping exists, computes the current frame from elapsed_ms and the frame range. If no mapping exists, the child is not rendered.

### MovementSystem

Runs when current phase is movement. Updates VisualEntity offsets by interpolating between previous position and current model position based on phase progress.

### AttackSystem

Runs when current phase is attack. Updates weapon child offsets to move from their start position toward the attack target's position based on phase progress. Attack animations move the offset ÔÇö they do not stretch the assets.

### ReactionSystem

Runs when current phase is reaction. For units that were hit, transitions body child from normal appearance to hit appearance over the first half, and back to normal over the second half.

### DefeatSystem

Runs when current phase is defeat. For units that died, applies shrink animation to the body child. Weapon child has no defeated animation defined, so it is not rendered.

### Renderer

Runs every frame. For each VisualEntity, iterates children by draw order. For each visible child, computes screen position (parent position + offset) and draws the current frame from the sprite sheet.

---

## Phase Animations

### Movement Phase (250ms)

During the movement phase a unit moves from its current position to its new position. During this time period the position of the unit is rendered based on how much time has passed. For example if 122ms/250ms has passed, the unit will show as 122/250 distance from their previous position to their new position. This is called a movement animation.

Movement is an animation with frames.

### Attack Phase (250ms)

During the attack phase, unit attack symbols move to intersect with their target. This is called an attack animation.

The archer's ranged attack needs to be large enough to cover full range (two linear squares away). There are three attack animations for the archer: one for adjacent attack, one for linear attack two squares away, and one for diagonal attack. These can all use the same sprite sheet with different indexes for first and last frame.

### Reaction Phase (250ms)

During the reaction phase, the unit transitions from its regular appearance to its hit appearance (if it was hit) over 50% of the time (125ms) and then transitions back to normal by the end of the reaction time (250ms total).

### Defeat Phase (250ms)

During the defeat phase, units that die shrink proportionally from full size to a small size.

---

## Visual Language

See `AvKrt-visual-states.pdf` for the full visual reference.

### Character Art

Innate capabilities (all units have these):
- **(Passive) Team**: Circle fill color. Blue = Knight, green = Archer.
- **(Action) Move**: All units can move.

Capabilities (one per unit, mutually exclusive):
- **(Action) Melee Attack**: Shorter arrow inside the circle. Represents knight melee attack capability.
- **(Action) Ranged Attack**: Longer arrow inside the circle. Represents archer ranged attack capability.

### Gameplay States

**Perform Melee Attack**: Attack indicator rotates to face target, moves out to intersect target.

**Receive Melee Attack**: Lightens to communicate being hit.

**Perform Ranged Attack**: Attack indicator rotates to face target, extends to intersect target.

**Receive Ranged Attack**: Lightens to communicate being hit.

**Knight Defeat**: Weapon disappears. Shrinks over 250ms then disappears.

**Archer Defeat**: Weapon disappears. Shrinks over 250ms then disappears.

---

## What Stays the Same

Everything in the [AvK spec](../../avk/docs/SPEC.md) that is not listed above.
name: ArcherVisual
abstract: true
components:
  VisualState: { state: 0 }
  PrevPosition: { x: 0, y: 0 }
  AttackTarget: { target_id: 0 }
  Scale: { value: 1.0 }
name: KnightVisual
abstract: true
components:
  VisualState: { state: 0 }
  PrevPosition: { x: 0, y: 0 }
  AttackTarget: { target_id: 0 }
  Scale: { value: 1.0 }
name: ViewConfig
components:
  TurnTiming:
    turn_length_ms: 1000
    movement_ms: 250
    attack_ms: 250
    reaction_ms: 250
    defeat_ms: 250
  PhaseState:
    current_phase: 0
    elapsed_ms: 0
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Archers vs Knights RT</title>
<style>
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
html, body { height: 100%; overflow: hidden; }
body {
    background: #1a1a2e;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    height: 100vh;
}
#header-area {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    gap: 16px; overflow: hidden;
}
#header-area h1 { font-size: 1.4em; color: #f0f0f0; white-space: nowrap; }
#status { font-size: 0.95em; color: #aaa; white-space: nowrap; }
#game-over-msg { font-size: 1.1em; font-weight: bold; color: #ffd700; }
#middle { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
canvas { border: 1px solid #333; border-radius: 4px; image-rendering: pixelated; }
#footer-area {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; overflow: hidden;
}
button {
    background: #2a2a4a; color: #e0e0e0; border: 1px solid #444;
    border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 0.9em;
    cursor: pointer; min-width: 70px;
}
button:hover { background: #3a3a5a; }
button.active { background: #4a6a4a; border-color: #6a8a6a; }
#legend { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; }
#legend span { margin: 0 8px; }
.green { color: #78be64; }
.blue { color: #4d94d2; }
#version { font-size: 0.6em; color: #555; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="header-area">
    <h1>Archers vs Knights RT</h1>
    <div id="status">Loading...</div>
    <div id="game-over-msg"></div>
</div>
<div id="middle">
    <canvas id="canvas" width="3072" height="1728"></canvas>
</div>
<div id="footer-area">
    <button id="btn-play" title="Space">Play</button>
    <button id="btn-step" title="Right Arrow">Step</button>
    <button id="btn-rewind" title="Left Arrow">Rewind</button>
    <button id="btn-new">New Game</button>
    <div id="legend">
        <span class="green">&#9679; Archer</span>
        <span class="blue">&#9679; Knight</span>
    </div>
    <div id="version">v0.0.14</div>
</div>

<script src="flecs-ecs.js"></script>
<script>
(function() {
    const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
    const statusEl = document.getElementById('status');
    const gameOverEl = document.getElementById('game-over-msg');
    const btnPlay = document.getElementById('btn-play');
    const btnStep = document.getElementById('btn-step');
    const btnRewind = document.getElementById('btn-rewind');
    const btnNew = document.getElementById('btn-new');
    const headerEl = document.getElementById('header-area');
    const middleEl = document.getElementById('middle');
    const footerEl = document.getElementById('footer-area');

    const CELL = 64, COLS = 48, ROWS = 27;
    const BG = '#0f0f23';

    let engine = null;
    let playing = false;
    let mapLabel = '';

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Turn timing ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    const PHASE_MS = 125;
    const PHASES = ['movement', 'attack', 'reaction', 'defeat'];

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ View state (persistent across turns) ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    let viewUnits = [];       /* persistent view units, keyed by entityId */
    let currentPhase = -1;    /* -1=idle, 0-3=animating phase */
    let phaseStartTime = 0;
    let animating = false;

    /* Read all units from WASM into a map keyed by entity_id */
    function readUnits() {
        const map = {};
        const count = engine.getUnitCount();
        for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
            const eid = engine.getEntityId(i);
            map[eid] = {
                entityId: eid,
                x: engine.getUnitX(i),
                y: engine.getUnitY(i),
                health: engine.getHealth(i),
                faction: engine.getUnitFaction(i),
                damaged: engine.getUnitDamaged(i),
                attackedId: engine.getAttackedId(i),
            };
        }
        return map;
    }

    /* Create a new view unit */
    function makeViewUnit(entityId, x, y, faction) {
        return {
            entityId: entityId,
            x: x, y: y,
            prevX: x, prevY: y,
            faction: faction,
            health: 0,
            wasDamaged: false,
            isDying: false,
            dead: false,
            attackedId: 0,
            attackAngle: 0,
        };
    }

    /* Initialize view from ModelWorld (used on game start and rewind) */
    function initViewFromModel() {
        const model = readUnits();
        viewUnits = [];
        for (const eid in model) {
            const m = model[eid];
            if (m.health <= 0) continue; /* skip dead units waiting for despawn */
            const vu = makeViewUnit(m.entityId, m.x, m.y, m.faction);
            vu.health = m.health;
            viewUnits.push(vu);
        }
    }

    /* Update persistent view units from ModelWorld after a turn */
    function updateViewForTurn() {
        const model = readUnits();
        const viewById = {};
        for (const vu of viewUnits) viewById[vu.entityId] = vu;

        /* Update existing view units with new model state */
        for (const eid in model) {
            const m = model[eid];
            let vu = viewById[eid];

            if (!vu) {
                /* New unit (spawned this turn) */
                vu = makeViewUnit(m.entityId, m.x, m.y, m.faction);
                viewUnits.push(vu);
                viewById[eid] = vu;
            }

            /* Store previous position (where the view unit currently is) */
            vu.prevX = vu.x;
            vu.prevY = vu.y;

            /* Update to new model state */
            vu.x = m.x;
            vu.y = m.y;
            vu.health = m.health;
            vu.wasDamaged = m.damaged;
            vu.isDying = m.health <= 0;
            vu.attackedId = m.attackedId;
            vu.attackAngle = 0;
        }

        /* Mark units that were despawned (in view but not in model) as dead.
           These already played their defeat animation last turn. */
        for (const vu of viewUnits) {
            if (!model[vu.entityId] && !vu.dead) {
                vu.dead = true;
            }
        }

        /* Remove dead units (defeat animation already played) */
        viewUnits = viewUnits.filter(vu => !vu.dead);

        /* Compute attack angles */
        const byId = {};
        for (const vu of viewUnits) byId[vu.entityId] = vu;
        for (const vu of viewUnits) {
            if (vu.attackedId && byId[vu.attackedId]) {
                const target = byId[vu.attackedId];
                vu.attackAngle = Math.atan2(target.y - vu.y, target.x - vu.x) + Math.PI / 2;
            }
        }
    }

    /* Find a view unit by entity_id */
    function findViewUnit(entityId) {
        return viewUnits.find(u => u.entityId === entityId);
    }

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Layout ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    const HEADER_MIN = 40, HEADER_MAX = 60;
    const FOOTER_MIN = 40, FOOTER_MAX = 60;
    const GAME_MIN = 240, GAME_ASPECT = 16 / 9;

    function layout() {
        const totalH = window.innerHeight, totalW = window.innerWidth;
        const chromeMin = HEADER_MIN + FOOTER_MIN;
        let headerH, footerH, gameH;
        if (totalH <= chromeMin) {
            headerH = totalH / 2; footerH = totalH / 2; gameH = 0;
        } else if (totalH < chromeMin + GAME_MIN) {
            headerH = HEADER_MIN; footerH = FOOTER_MIN; gameH = totalH - chromeMin;
        } else {
            const avail = totalH - chromeMin - GAME_MIN;
            const extra = (HEADER_MAX - HEADER_MIN) + (FOOTER_MAX - FOOTER_MIN);
            const t = Math.min(1, avail / extra);
            headerH = HEADER_MIN + (HEADER_MAX - HEADER_MIN) * t;
            footerH = FOOTER_MIN + (FOOTER_MAX - FOOTER_MIN) * t;
            gameH = totalH - headerH - footerH;
        }
        headerEl.style.height = Math.floor(headerH) + 'px';
        footerEl.style.height = Math.floor(footerH) + 'px';
        middleEl.style.height = Math.floor(gameH) + 'px';
        let cw = gameH * GAME_ASPECT, ch = gameH;
        if (cw > totalW) { cw = totalW; ch = cw / GAME_ASPECT; }
        canvas.style.width = Math.floor(cw) + 'px';
        canvas.style.height = Math.floor(ch) + 'px';
    }
    layout();
    window.addEventListener('resize', layout);

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Sprites ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    const SPRITE_NAMES = ['knight_body', 'archer_body', 'knight_weapon', 'archer_weapon'];
    const SPRITE_COUNTS = { knight_body: 17, archer_body: 17, knight_weapon: 1, archer_weapon: 1 };
    const sprites = {};
    let spritesLoaded = 0, spritesTotal = 0;

    function loadSprites(basePath, cb) {
        for (const name of SPRITE_NAMES) {
            const count = SPRITE_COUNTS[name];
            spritesTotal += count;
            sprites[name] = { frames: [] };
            for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
                const img = new Image();
                img.onload = img.onerror = function() { spritesLoaded++; if (spritesLoaded === spritesTotal) cb(); };
                img.src = `${basePath}/${name}/frame_${String(i).padStart(2,'0')}.png`;
                sprites[name].frames.push(img);
            }
        }
    }

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Rendering ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    function drawGrid() {
        ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.08)';
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        for (let x = 0; x <= COLS; x++) { ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x*CELL,0); ctx.lineTo(x*CELL,ROWS*CELL); ctx.stroke(); }
        for (let y = 0; y <= ROWS; y++) { ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(0,y*CELL); ctx.lineTo(COLS*CELL,y*CELL); ctx.stroke(); }
    }

    function drawUnit(u, phase, t) {
        const bodyName = u.faction === 0 ? 'archer_body' : 'knight_body';
        const weaponName = u.faction === 0 ? 'archer_weapon' : 'knight_weapon';
        let drawX, drawY, bodyFrame = 0, scale = 1, showWeapon = true;
        let weaponOffX = 0, weaponOffY = 0;

        switch (phase) {
            case 'movement':
                drawX = (u.prevX + (u.x - u.prevX) * t - 1) * CELL;
                drawY = (u.prevY + (u.y - u.prevY) * t - 1) * CELL;
                break;

            case 'attack':
                drawX = (u.x - 1) * CELL;
                drawY = (u.y - 1) * CELL;
                /* Animate weapon toward target */
                if (u.attackedId) {
                    const target = findViewUnit(u.attackedId);
                    if (target) {
                        weaponOffX = (target.x - u.x) * CELL * t;
                        weaponOffY = (target.y - u.y) * CELL * t;
                    }
                }
                break;

            case 'reaction':
                drawX = (u.x - 1) * CELL;
                drawY = (u.y - 1) * CELL;
                if (u.wasDamaged) {
                    /* frames 1-8: lighten then return */
                    bodyFrame = 1 + Math.min(7, Math.floor(t * 8));
                }
                break;

            case 'defeat':
                drawX = (u.x - 1) * CELL;
                drawY = (u.y - 1) * CELL;
                if (u.isDying) {
                    bodyFrame = 9 + Math.min(7, Math.floor(t * 8));
                    scale = 1 - t * 0.9;
                    showWeapon = false;
                }
                break;

            default: /* idle */
                drawX = (u.x - 1) * CELL;
                drawY = (u.y - 1) * CELL;
        }

        /* Draw body */
        const bodyImg = sprites[bodyName].frames[Math.min(bodyFrame, sprites[bodyName].frames.length - 1)];
        if (bodyImg && bodyImg.complete) {
            const size = CELL * scale;
            const off = (CELL - size) / 2;
            ctx.drawImage(bodyImg, drawX + off, drawY + off, size, size);
        }

        /* Draw weapon (rotated to face attack target) */
        if (showWeapon) {
            const wImg = sprites[weaponName].frames[0];
            if (wImg && wImg.complete) {
                const size = CELL * scale;
                const cx = drawX + CELL / 2 + weaponOffX;
                const cy = drawY + CELL / 2 + weaponOffY;
                ctx.save();
                ctx.translate(cx, cy);
                if (u.attackAngle) ctx.rotate(u.attackAngle);
                ctx.drawImage(wImg, -size / 2, -size / 2, size, size);
                ctx.restore();
            }
        }
    }

    function render(timestamp) {
        if (!engine) return;

        ctx.fillStyle = BG;
        ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
        drawGrid();

        const phase = currentPhase >= 0 ? PHASES[currentPhase] : 'idle';
        let t = 0;
        if (currentPhase >= 0 && phaseStartTime > 0) {
            t = Math.min(1, (timestamp - phaseStartTime) / PHASE_MS);
        }

        for (const u of viewUnits) {
            if (u.dead) continue;
            drawUnit(u, phase, t);
        }

        /* Status */
        const turn = engine.getTurn();
        const gameOver = engine.isGameOver();
        if (gameOver) gameOverEl.textContent = engine.getMessage();
        const aliveCount = viewUnits.filter(u => !u.dead && !u.isDying).length;
        const phaseLabel = currentPhase >= 0 ? ` | ${phase} ${Math.floor(t*100)}%` : '';
        statusEl.textContent = `${mapLabel} | Turn ${turn} | ${aliveCount} units${phaseLabel}`;

        /* Phase progression */
        if (currentPhase >= 0) {
            if (t >= 1) {
                currentPhase++;
                if (currentPhase >= PHASES.length) {
                    currentPhase = -1;
                    animating = false;
                    /* Mark dying units as dead ÔÇö they'll be removed at next turn start */
                    for (const u of viewUnits) {
                        if (u.isDying) u.dead = true;
                    }
                    if (playing && !gameOver) {
                        startTurn();
                    }
                    return;
                }
                phaseStartTime = timestamp;
            }
            requestAnimationFrame(render);
        }
    }

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Controls ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    function startTurn() {
        if (!engine || engine.isGameOver() || animating) return;
        animating = true;
        engine.turn();
        updateViewForTurn();
        currentPhase = 0;
        phaseStartTime = performance.now();
        requestAnimationFrame(render);
    }

    function togglePlay() {
        playing = !playing;
        btnPlay.textContent = playing ? 'Pause' : 'Play';
        btnPlay.classList.toggle('active', playing);
        if (playing && !animating) startTurn();
    }

    function rewindOne() {
        if (!engine || animating) return;
        const turn = engine.getTurn();
        if (turn > 1) {
            engine.rewind(turn - 1);
            gameOverEl.textContent = '';
            initViewFromModel();
            currentPhase = -1;
            requestAnimationFrame(render);
        }
    }

    function newGame() {
        if (playing) togglePlay();
        animating = false;
        currentPhase = -1;
        gameOverEl.textContent = '';
        engine.initWithConfig('wasm-rt');
        initViewFromModel();
        requestAnimationFrame(render);
    }

    btnPlay.addEventListener('click', togglePlay);
    btnStep.addEventListener('click', startTurn);
    btnRewind.addEventListener('click', rewindOne);
    btnNew.addEventListener('click', newGame);
    document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
        if (e.code === 'Space') { e.preventDefault(); togglePlay(); }
        else if (e.code === 'ArrowRight') { e.preventDefault(); startTurn(); }
        else if (e.code === 'ArrowLeft') { e.preventDefault(); rewindOne(); }
    });

    /* ÔöÇÔöÇ Init ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ */
    statusEl.textContent = 'Loading sprites...';
    loadSprites('assets/sprites', function() {
        statusEl.textContent = 'Loading engine...';
        FlecsECS().then(function(M) {
            engine = {
                init: M.cwrap('wasm_init', 'number', []),
                initWithConfig: M.cwrap('wasm_init_with_config', 'number', ['string']),
                turn: M.cwrap('wasm_turn', 'number', []),
                getTurn: M.cwrap('wasm_get_turn', 'number', []),
                getUnitCount: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_count', 'number', []),
                getUnitX: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_x', 'number', ['number']),
                getUnitY: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_y', 'number', ['number']),
                getUnitFaction: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_faction', 'number', ['number']),
                getUnitDamaged: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_took_damage', 'number', ['number']),
                getHealth: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_health', 'number', ['number']),
                getAttackedId: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_attacked_id', 'number', ['number']),
                getEntityId: M.cwrap('wasm_get_unit_entity_id', 'number', ['number']),
                getMapX: M.cwrap('wasm_get_map_x', 'number', []),
                getMapY: M.cwrap('wasm_get_map_y', 'number', []),
                isGameOver: M.cwrap('wasm_is_game_over', 'number', []),
                getMessage: M.cwrap('wasm_get_game_over_message', 'string', []),
                rewind: M.cwrap('wasm_rewind', 'number', ['number']),
                reset: M.cwrap('wasm_reset', 'number', []),
            };
            engine.initWithConfig('wasm-rt');
            const mx = engine.getMapX();
            const my = engine.getMapY();
            mapLabel = `${mx}x${my} map`;
            initViewFromModel();
            requestAnimationFrame(render);
        });
    });
})();
</script>
</body>
</html>
name: animation
description: >
  Runs every frame. For every visual child, looks up the parent's
  current state in the child's StateAnimations. If a mapping exists,
  computes the current frame from elapsed_ms and the frame range.
  If no mapping exists, the child is not rendered (visible = false).
enabled: true
name: attack_phase
description: >
  Runs when current phase is attack. Updates weapon child offsets
  to move from start position toward AttackTarget position based
  on phase progress. Moves the offset, does not stretch assets.
enabled: true
name: defeat_phase
description: >
  Runs when current phase is defeat. For units with IsDying,
  applies shrink animation to body child (Scale decreases from 1 to 0).
  Weapon child has no defeated animation, so it is not rendered.
enabled: true
name: movement_phase
description: >
  Runs when current phase is movement. Updates VisualEntity offsets
  by interpolating between PrevPosition and current ModelWorld
  Location based on phase progress.
enabled: true
name: phase_advance
description: >
  Runs every frame. Increments PhaseState.elapsed_ms by delta time.
  When elapsed >= phase duration, advances to the next phase and
  updates all VisualEntity states. After all four phases complete,
  signals the ModelWorld to advance the next turn.
enabled: true
name: reaction_phase
description: >
  Runs when current phase is reaction. For units with WasHit,
  transitions body child from normal appearance to hit appearance
  over first 50% of phase, then back to normal over second 50%.
enabled: true
name: renderer
description: >
  Runs every frame. For each VisualEntity, iterates children by
  DrawOrder. For each visible child (AnimationState.visible = true),
  computes screen position (parent position + Offset) and draws
  the current frame from the sprite sheet.
enabled: true
name: turn_capture
description: >
  Runs once after the ModelWorld advances a turn.
  Creates/destroys VisualEntities to match ModelWorld population.
  For each unit: reads previous position from rewind history,
  copies Weapon.attacked to AttackTarget, checks TookDamage -> WasHit,
  checks health <= 0 -> IsDying.
  Sets all VisualEntity states to movement phase.
enabled: true
"""Generate sprite sheet frames for AvK RT.

All frames are 64x64 PNG with transparent backgrounds.
Animations at 30fps. Phase duration 250ms = ~8 frames per phase.

Sprite sheets:
  knight_body/  ÔÇö blue circle: idle, hit, defeat (shrink)
  archer_body/  ÔÇö green circle: idle, hit, defeat (shrink)
  knight_weapon/ ÔÇö short arrow (melee), pointing up, centered
  archer_weapon/ ÔÇö long arrow (ranged), pointing up, centered

Arrows point up (north). The renderer rotates to face the target.
"""

from PIL import Image, ImageDraw
import os
import math

SIZE = 64
FPS = 30
PHASE_MS = 250
PHASE_FRAMES = round(PHASE_MS * FPS / 1000)  # 8 frames per phase

SCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))
ASSETS = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, "..", "assets", "sprites")

# Colors from the PDF
KNIGHT_FILL = (77, 148, 210, 180)      # blue fill (semi-transparent)
KNIGHT_STROKE = (60, 120, 190, 255)    # blue outline
KNIGHT_HIT = (160, 200, 235, 180)      # lightened blue

ARCHER_FILL = (120, 190, 100, 180)     # green fill (semi-transparent)
ARCHER_STROKE = (90, 160, 70, 255)     # green outline
ARCHER_HIT = (185, 225, 170, 180)      # lightened green

ARROW_KNIGHT = (70, 150, 220, 255)     # blue arrow
ARROW_ARCHER = (80, 160, 60, 255)      # dark green arrow

TRANSPARENT = (0, 0, 0, 0)
STROKE_W = 3


def new_frame():
    return Image.new("RGBA", (SIZE, SIZE), TRANSPARENT)


def save_frame(img, directory, index):
    path = os.path.join(directory, f"frame_{index:02d}.png")
    img.save(path)


def draw_body_circle(img, fill, stroke, scale=1.0):
    """Draw a circle centered in the frame with optional scale."""
    d = ImageDraw.Draw(img)
    radius = int(28 * scale)
    if radius < 1:
        return
    cx, cy = SIZE // 2, SIZE // 2
    bbox = [cx - radius, cy - radius, cx + radius, cy + radius]
    d.ellipse(bbox, fill=fill, outline=stroke, width=STROKE_W)


def draw_arrow(img, color, length, width=6):
    """Draw an arrow pointing up, centered horizontally, tip near top."""
    d = ImageDraw.Draw(img)
    cx = SIZE // 2
    tip_y = SIZE // 2 - length // 2
    base_y = SIZE // 2 + length // 2

    # Shaft
    d.line([(cx, tip_y + 8), (cx, base_y)], fill=color, width=3)

    # Arrowhead
    d.polygon([
        (cx, tip_y),
        (cx - width, tip_y + 10),
        (cx + width, tip_y + 10),
    ], fill=color)


def generate_body(name, fill, stroke, hit_fill, arrow_color, arrow_length):
    outdir = os.path.join(ASSETS, name)
    os.makedirs(outdir, exist_ok=True)

    frame_idx = 0

    # --- Idle: 1 frame ---
    img = new_frame()
    draw_body_circle(img, fill, stroke)
    save_frame(img, outdir, frame_idx)
    frame_idx += 1

    # --- Hit: 8 frames (lighten then return) ---
    for i in range(PHASE_FRAMES):
        t = i / (PHASE_FRAMES - 1) if PHASE_FRAMES > 1 else 0
        # First half: normal -> hit, second half: hit -> normal
        if t <= 0.5:
            blend = t * 2  # 0 to 1
        else:
            blend = (1 - t) * 2  # 1 to 0

        r = int(fill[0] + (hit_fill[0] - fill[0]) * blend)
        g = int(fill[1] + (hit_fill[1] - fill[1]) * blend)
        b = int(fill[2] + (hit_fill[2] - fill[2]) * blend)
        a = int(fill[3] + (hit_fill[3] - fill[3]) * blend)

        img = new_frame()
        draw_body_circle(img, (r, g, b, a), stroke)
        save_frame(img, outdir, frame_idx)
        frame_idx += 1

    # --- Defeat: 8 frames (shrink from full to tiny) ---
    for i in range(PHASE_FRAMES):
        t = i / (PHASE_FRAMES - 1) if PHASE_FRAMES > 1 else 0
        scale = 1.0 - t * 0.9  # shrink to 10% size

        img = new_frame()
        draw_body_circle(img, fill, stroke, scale=scale)
        save_frame(img, outdir, frame_idx)
        frame_idx += 1

    print(f"  {name}: {frame_idx} frames")
    return frame_idx


def generate_weapon(name, color, length):
    outdir = os.path.join(ASSETS, name)
    os.makedirs(outdir, exist_ok=True)

    # Single frame ÔÇö idle arrow pointing up
    img = new_frame()
    draw_arrow(img, color, length)
    save_frame(img, outdir, 0)

    print(f"  {name}: 1 frame")


def generate_manifest(name, frame_count, animations):
    """Write a YAML manifest for a sprite sheet."""
    path = os.path.join(ASSETS, name, "sheet.yaml")
    with open(path, "w") as f:
        f.write(f"name: {name}\n")
        f.write(f"frame_size: {SIZE}\n")
        f.write(f"frame_count: {frame_count}\n")
        f.write(f"fps: {FPS}\n")
        f.write(f"animations:\n")
        for anim_name, first, last in animations:
            f.write(f"  {anim_name}:\n")
            f.write(f"    first_frame: {first}\n")
            f.write(f"    last_frame: {last}\n")


print("Generating sprites...")

# Body sprites
knight_frames = generate_body("knight_body", KNIGHT_FILL, KNIGHT_STROKE,
                               KNIGHT_HIT, ARROW_KNIGHT, 20)
generate_manifest("knight_body", knight_frames, [
    ("idle", 0, 0),
    ("hit", 1, PHASE_FRAMES),
    ("defeat", PHASE_FRAMES + 1, PHASE_FRAMES * 2),
])

archer_frames = generate_body("archer_body", ARCHER_FILL, ARCHER_STROKE,
                               ARCHER_HIT, ARROW_ARCHER, 30)
generate_manifest("archer_body", archer_frames, [
    ("idle", 0, 0),
    ("hit", 1, PHASE_FRAMES),
    ("defeat", PHASE_FRAMES + 1, PHASE_FRAMES * 2),
])

# Weapon sprites (single frame, rotated at render time)
generate_weapon("knight_weapon", ARROW_KNIGHT, 20)
generate_manifest("knight_weapon", 1, [
    ("idle", 0, 0),
])

generate_weapon("archer_weapon", ARROW_ARCHER, 30)
generate_manifest("archer_weapon", 1, [
    ("idle", 0, 0),
])

print(f"\nDone. Sprites written to {ASSETS}/")
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
